Wins

00:01:09.210 --> 00:01:11.760
Oh, Nature-sensei...

00:01:16.110 --> 00:01:19.170
Help, please!

00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:47.670
Umamusume

00:01:41.240 --> 00:01:47.670
Pretty Derby

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:54.770
Oshiruko

00:02:52.250 --> 00:02:53.350
Here.

00:02:53.350 --> 00:02:54.770
Thank you...

00:02:54.770 --> 00:02:58.800
Episode 8
What's Always Been There

00:02:55.250 --> 00:02:57.680
So, what's going on?

00:02:58.010 --> 00:03:00.910
Well, it's about Dia-chan.

00:03:00.910 --> 00:03:03.510
What, did you get into a fight?

00:03:03.510 --> 00:03:06.210
Not exactly, but...

00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:10.460
She completely beat me at the Arima Kinen.

00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:11.570
You really think it was that bad?

00:03:11.570 --> 00:03:15.960
It was by a neck's difference, right?
That sounds like a good race to me.

00:03:15.960 --> 00:03:17.380
Look.

00:03:17.690 --> 00:03:20.900
"If they had raced ten times, the outcome
could have been different in each case—

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:24.890
that was how tightly contested
and entertaining this race was."

00:03:24.890 --> 00:03:26.520
That's what most people think.

00:03:26.520 --> 00:03:28.390
And I agree with them.

00:03:28.930 --> 00:03:30.500
What's wrong?

00:03:31.160 --> 00:03:35.230
Did you lose your confidence, like last year?

00:03:35.750 --> 00:03:37.650
It's not like that.

00:03:37.650 --> 00:03:42.410
Less a loss of confidence and
more like... Dia-chan...

00:03:42.410 --> 00:03:43.160
Yeah?

00:03:43.980 --> 00:03:46.880
Dia-chan was so strong.

00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:52.440
Even before we raced,
her aura was like... crackling.

00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:53.290
Crackling?

00:03:53.660 --> 00:03:56.230
And during the race, I got chills.

00:03:56.230 --> 00:04:00.460
Despite how close I was, it didn't
feel like I could catch up at all...

00:04:01.080 --> 00:04:02.180
She felt so far away.

00:04:10.090 --> 00:04:11.480
It's gonna be okay!

00:04:12.330 --> 00:04:14.660
You were plenty strong yourself.

00:04:14.660 --> 00:04:17.490
In my opinion, anyway.

00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:18.850
Nature-san...

00:04:18.850 --> 00:04:22.150
The first step is drinking that
and feeling a little better.

00:04:22.150 --> 00:04:23.730
It's nice and sweet.

00:04:24.230 --> 00:04:25.740
You're right.

00:04:25.740 --> 00:04:28.340
Thank you so much, Sensei.

00:04:28.340 --> 00:04:29.600
Sensei?

00:04:30.410 --> 00:04:32.620
No, don't worry about it.

00:04:35.620 --> 00:04:37.880
Oshiruko

00:04:46.390 --> 00:04:48.650
Things are so lively.

00:04:48.650 --> 00:04:49.760
Yeah...

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:52.980
Where should we start?
Maybe by visiting the shrine?

00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:57.020
Kita-chan?

00:04:57.230 --> 00:04:58.500
What's wrong?

00:04:58.500 --> 00:05:01.010
Uh, no, it's nothing!

00:05:01.010 --> 00:05:02.060
Are you sure?

00:05:02.060 --> 00:05:03.400
Yeah, I'm sure!

00:05:02.540 --> 00:05:04.140
Step right up!

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:05.150
Okay...

00:05:05.150 --> 00:05:07.360
We've got amazake over here!

00:05:07.910 --> 00:05:10.410
Come and get yourself a drink!

00:05:10.410 --> 00:05:13.120
Look, Dia-chan, they're selling amazake!

00:05:10.410 --> 00:05:16.320
It'll warm you up! It's tasty,
and we've got the best stuff!

00:05:13.120 --> 00:05:14.280
I'm gonna get some!

00:05:14.790 --> 00:05:17.350
Excuse me! One amazake please!

00:05:17.350 --> 00:05:18.760
Welcome!

00:05:18.760 --> 00:05:20.330
It'll be a thousand yen.

00:05:36.190 --> 00:05:38.500
We're glad you could make it.

00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:41.770
You'll find all of our
charms are a blessed value!

00:05:38.980 --> 00:05:40.980
Luck for victory

00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:43.190
Okay!

00:05:43.610 --> 00:05:44.840
I'll take this one.

00:05:44.840 --> 00:05:45.610
Sure.

00:05:45.610 --> 00:05:47.110
That's the last one!

00:05:49.180 --> 00:05:53.510
Hey, Kita-chan, what kind
of charm did you get?

00:05:53.510 --> 00:05:55.750
Well... one for victory.

00:05:55.750 --> 00:05:56.870
Really?

00:05:56.870 --> 00:05:59.120
We match, then! That's great.

00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:01.380
Luck for victory

00:05:59.410 --> 00:06:01.380
Y-Yeah...

00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:05.940
Luck for victory

00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:06.190
Hey, Dia-chan, what were
you wishing for this year?

00:06:06.190 --> 00:06:07.130
Why are you asking?

00:06:07.130 --> 00:06:11.560
Well... It felt like you were
putting a lot of thought into it.

00:06:11.560 --> 00:06:15.640
I-I just wished to win a lot!

00:06:18.170 --> 00:06:20.900
I want to win the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:06:22.020 --> 00:06:25.120
Remember how Crown-chan won
a G1 race in Hong Kong?

00:06:25.120 --> 00:06:29.280
Seeing that made me want to
try racing on the global level.

00:06:29.650 --> 00:06:32.030
And you picked the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe?

00:06:32.030 --> 00:06:32.790
Yeah.

00:06:33.120 --> 00:06:35.530
A Japanese runner has never
won it before, right?

00:06:35.940 --> 00:06:39.030
Every time someone tries, people get
their hopes up, but it doesn't work out.

00:06:39.370 --> 00:06:42.420
Some people even say
it'll never happen.

00:06:42.910 --> 00:06:43.790
Which is why...

00:06:44.270 --> 00:06:49.170
I think it'd be really meaningful
if I won that particular race.

00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:52.930
As a member of the Satono Group,
I want to accomplish something.

00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:56.310
The kind of accomplishment that will leave
a mark on the Japanese horse girl world

00:06:56.310 --> 00:06:58.180
that'll be remembered in the future.

00:07:03.970 --> 00:07:05.110
They're the same.

00:07:05.610 --> 00:07:08.950
Hey, Kita-chan, you should come
with me. Let's race in France!

00:07:08.950 --> 00:07:11.070
Me too?!

00:07:11.070 --> 00:07:11.930
Yeah!

00:07:11.930 --> 00:07:13.740
W-Well...

00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:17.390
I'd love for you to be there too.

00:07:17.390 --> 00:07:19.710
And together we can represent Japan

00:07:19.710 --> 00:07:22.580
and take on the strongest
horse girls in the world!

00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:26.210
Let's see what's out there!

00:07:26.210 --> 00:07:28.160
S-Sure...

00:07:28.630 --> 00:07:31.590
I get it now. Dia-chan is...

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:34.690
a lot like Dura-chan.

00:07:47.380 --> 00:07:48.950
You can't lose your cool.

00:07:50.690 --> 00:07:51.940
Sis?

00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:54.660
You need to follow through better.

00:07:55.170 --> 00:07:56.660
Let's switch pitchers.

00:08:10.480 --> 00:08:11.470
Yes!

00:08:11.470 --> 00:08:13.080
What are you doing here?

00:08:13.690 --> 00:08:14.840
Nothing in particular.

00:08:15.430 --> 00:08:17.350
I don't need to be cheered up.

00:08:18.900 --> 00:08:21.220
You make everything so complicated.

00:08:21.220 --> 00:08:24.550
And here I thought I could
buy you some new shoes.

00:08:24.550 --> 00:08:25.400
It's fine.

00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:26.730
Aw, come on...

00:08:27.170 --> 00:08:29.490
Just let me spoil you once in a while.

00:08:29.490 --> 00:08:31.510
I'm not like Vivlos.

00:08:33.020 --> 00:08:34.270
Or you.

00:08:43.050 --> 00:08:44.340
We are alike.

00:08:44.740 --> 00:08:46.630
We both have trouble winning.

00:08:50.160 --> 00:08:52.260
What did you want to talk about?

00:08:52.260 --> 00:08:55.750
Well... how's your recovery going?

00:08:56.260 --> 00:08:58.410
I'm still not fully healed.

00:08:59.310 --> 00:09:00.760
I see.

00:09:01.260 --> 00:09:03.290
It's just a matter of time.

00:09:03.930 --> 00:09:05.910
I'll heal. I know it.

00:09:06.270 --> 00:09:09.940
My duty is to prove I am
the strongest in the world.

00:09:10.360 --> 00:09:15.760
And one day, as my bloodline
dictates, I will conquer the world.

00:09:16.520 --> 00:09:19.410
I won't let this slow me down.

00:09:22.470 --> 00:09:24.700
You really are amazing.

00:09:24.700 --> 00:09:25.980
I am?

00:09:25.980 --> 00:09:28.740
I mean the way you're so
direct about it, Dura-chan.

00:09:29.150 --> 00:09:30.380
Of course.

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:33.090
It's my reason for running.

00:09:33.610 --> 00:09:36.170
Yeah, that makes sense.

00:09:36.170 --> 00:09:37.910
What are you looking toward?

00:09:38.840 --> 00:09:41.450
What's at the end of your path?

00:09:42.260 --> 00:09:43.850
I mean...

00:09:43.850 --> 00:09:47.460
What is your shining,
ultimate reward in the distance?

00:09:47.460 --> 00:09:49.110
The thing you want to accomplish?

00:09:49.570 --> 00:09:52.370
Basically, your own reason for running.

00:09:52.370 --> 00:09:55.150
Well, my reason for running...

00:09:55.150 --> 00:09:57.470
I guess because I want to win?

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:00.020
Then what?

00:10:01.680 --> 00:10:03.460
The thing you can't help but chase,

00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:06.900
and won't allow yourself to stop until
you have it. The thing you need.

00:10:07.270 --> 00:10:08.120
I know you have something.

00:10:32.600 --> 00:10:36.110
I never thought about taking
on the world before.

00:10:37.800 --> 00:10:41.200
Dia-chan and Dura-chan are both so amazing.

00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:46.830
Something I need to have...

00:10:47.780 --> 00:10:50.260
Until recently...

00:10:52.250 --> 00:10:54.610
I wanted to be like Teio-san.

00:10:55.090 --> 00:11:00.590
Can this emperor
surpass the last?

00:10:55.090 --> 00:11:00.590
Tokai Teio

00:10:55.510 --> 00:10:59.340
A glamorous star who's able
to make everyone smile.

00:11:01.280 --> 00:11:03.470
But... not anymore.

00:11:05.110 --> 00:11:08.570
Since I know I can't do it.

00:11:10.090 --> 00:11:14.960
So I decided to be true to
myself and train in my own way.

00:11:15.350 --> 00:11:17.470
I won. I won time and again.

00:11:18.410 --> 00:11:24.150
But wanting to dedicate everything
to a goal.

00:11:24.940 --> 00:11:30.320
A dream like that is not something I have anymore.

00:11:36.650 --> 00:11:39.130
Honey, honey, honey!

00:11:39.130 --> 00:11:42.130
When I get a taste of that honey...

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:44.640
Okay!

00:11:48.040 --> 00:11:50.150
Hey, Kita-chan! Welcome back.

00:11:50.150 --> 00:11:51.410
Teio-san...

00:11:51.410 --> 00:11:53.490
H-Hello there.

00:11:54.850 --> 00:11:57.690
Uh, well...

00:11:59.480 --> 00:12:01.290
What's wrong, Kita-chan?

00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:05.950
Umamusume

00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:05.950
Pretty Derby

00:12:06.530 --> 00:12:08.950
One, two, three, four,

00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:11.840
two, two, three, four...

00:12:11.840 --> 00:12:14.360
One, two, three, four...

00:12:13.480 --> 00:12:15.630
Say, Teio-san...

00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:22.590
Your dream... was to become an undefeated
Triple Crown horse girl, right?

00:12:22.830 --> 00:12:23.650
Yep.

00:12:23.980 --> 00:12:29.190
To be more specific, I wanted to
be a cool horse girl like the Prez.

00:12:29.190 --> 00:12:33.100
Have you ever seen her races before?
She was amazing!

00:12:33.690 --> 00:12:37.980
She was stronger, faster,
and sparkled more than anyone.

00:12:37.980 --> 00:12:42.380
I always used to talk about
how I wanted to be like her.

00:12:42.970 --> 00:12:46.490
I thought I was going to be an undefeated
Triple Crown horse girl for sure.

00:12:47.210 --> 00:12:49.900
Not that I actually pulled it off, though!

00:12:50.250 --> 00:12:52.160
But... even then...

00:12:52.780 --> 00:12:55.420
You kept running, right?

00:12:57.040 --> 00:12:58.420
Sure did.

00:12:58.420 --> 00:13:02.300
You always had some kind of
dream that you were chasing.

00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:05.180
How did you manage that?

00:13:08.190 --> 00:13:09.860
Let me think...

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:13.690
After I got injured and couldn't
manage the Triple Crown,

00:13:14.300 --> 00:13:17.060
I went to watch the Kikkashou.

00:13:17.610 --> 00:13:18.890
It was amazing.

00:13:19.250 --> 00:13:22.390
Everyone was running with
their pride and dreams on their shoulders,

00:13:22.390 --> 00:13:24.000
and they were so desperate to win.

00:13:24.690 --> 00:13:25.950
It was the coolest.

00:13:26.610 --> 00:13:28.480
It made me want to keep trying.

00:13:28.480 --> 00:13:30.000
Even though I couldn't win the triple crown,

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:33.870
it gave me the courage to think I could
still become an undefeated horse girl.

00:13:34.960 --> 00:13:40.710
I got discouraged and lost a few times
after that, and my dream even changed, but...

00:13:41.350 --> 00:13:42.340
Still...

00:13:43.040 --> 00:13:45.220
There was someone who became my goal.

00:13:46.650 --> 00:13:49.150
Another who told me not to give up.

00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:52.720
And one who gave me a good
luck charm, actually!

00:13:54.910 --> 00:14:00.150
I was able to keep moving forward because
of all of the people who supported me.

00:14:01.210 --> 00:14:02.510
And then, the day came—

00:14:10.830 --> 00:14:12.690
I was so happy.

00:14:13.240 --> 00:14:15.610
I felt like I had finally pulled it off.

00:14:16.800 --> 00:14:18.270
You had done it.

00:14:18.810 --> 00:14:19.590
So, then...

00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:24.400
I was satisfied with my dream
coming true... or so I thought,

00:14:24.710 --> 00:14:27.670
but I could feel something
inside of me bubbling up.

00:14:28.010 --> 00:14:30.750
A bubbling feeling?

00:14:30.750 --> 00:14:31.680
Yep.

00:14:32.360 --> 00:14:33.690
I wanted to keep running.

00:14:37.180 --> 00:14:38.560
I realized...

00:14:37.180 --> 00:14:39.190
Symboli Rudolf

00:14:37.180 --> 00:14:39.190
Dedicated
to victory

00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:41.190
Win the Arima Kinen!!

00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:44.720
that I still hadn't become a cool,
strong horse girl like the Prez.

00:14:45.940 --> 00:14:52.450
Symboli Rudolf

00:14:45.940 --> 00:14:52.450
Dedicated to victory

00:14:46.320 --> 00:14:52.100
I couldn't become an undefeated Triple
Crown winner, so I gave up on that dream.

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:57.940
But the truth is, deep down,
something was still smoldering.

00:15:00.940 --> 00:15:04.650
Which is why I decided to aim
for the Dream Trophy League.

00:15:05.090 --> 00:15:10.520
After all, I still want to be the
emperor who surpasses the last one.

00:15:11.220 --> 00:15:15.590
And no matter what happened...
that feeling would keep me running.

00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:20.640
Up we go!

00:15:21.480 --> 00:15:26.940
I'm not gonna ask what's got you worried,
Kita-chan, but I think you'll be okay.

00:15:28.080 --> 00:15:32.450
Because I'm sure you have something
like that which will never go away.

00:15:33.740 --> 00:15:35.050
Teio-san...

00:15:52.420 --> 00:15:54.270
Something that never goes away...

00:15:54.270 --> 00:15:57.710
One, two, three, four,

00:15:57.710 --> 00:16:01.560
two, two, three, four.

00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:04.680
One, two, three, four,

00:16:04.680 --> 00:16:07.770
two, two, three, four...

00:16:05.500 --> 00:16:07.770
Okay, next up is running.

00:16:07.770 --> 00:16:08.820
Okay!

00:16:09.540 --> 00:16:13.920
Something that was there in the
beginning... that I can't give up on.

00:16:17.120 --> 00:16:18.950
My dad's performances...

00:16:23.580 --> 00:16:29.130
Ever yone smiling, in that place
with such a warm atmosphere.

00:16:32.130 --> 00:16:33.890
Teio-san's races.

00:16:34.420 --> 00:16:38.700
The way that the heat from the crowd
churned in the air so intensely.

00:16:38.700 --> 00:16:41.240
It felt hot and lively.

00:16:42.710 --> 00:16:47.390
It was dazzling and so
bright it made me dizzy.

00:16:49.460 --> 00:16:51.990
It's the first thing that comes to mind.

00:16:52.230 --> 00:16:57.990
The sights and the sound... I remember
all of it so intensely that my chest hurts.

00:16:58.620 --> 00:17:03.000
I know it's impossible, but it
still sparkles so much.

00:17:03.610 --> 00:17:04.410
It's—

00:17:04.410 --> 00:17:07.000
We've got great prices for you!

00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:10.000
And for a limited time only,
they're even better!

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:15.310
Pick something up! I'd especially
recommend today's bananas!

00:17:15.310 --> 00:17:17.720
I'll make sure it's the
best performance possible!

00:17:17.720 --> 00:17:20.350
I'll make sure it's a memorable one!

00:17:21.530 --> 00:17:24.570
Come on over and pick
yourself up some bananas!

00:17:24.570 --> 00:17:26.350
Right over here!

00:17:26.350 --> 00:17:27.960
Hello there...

00:17:27.960 --> 00:17:29.730
Hey, Kita-chan! Welcome!

00:17:29.730 --> 00:17:32.950
Cold today, huh? Is that
tracksuit warm enough for you?

00:17:32.950 --> 00:17:34.740
Well, I was running.

00:17:34.740 --> 00:17:39.070
Oh, okay. In the middle of
a run, huh? Working hard!

00:17:39.070 --> 00:17:40.490
W-Well... no...

00:17:41.580 --> 00:17:44.560
Um, about the Arima—

00:17:44.560 --> 00:17:47.820
Oh, right! I had something
nice for you, Kita-chan!

00:17:48.970 --> 00:17:50.220
Give me one sec.

00:17:50.630 --> 00:17:53.610
Honey, could you get the thing we set aside?

00:17:53.610 --> 00:17:56.170
What thing is that?

00:17:56.170 --> 00:17:58.830
You know what thing I'm
talking about! For Kita-chan!

00:17:58.830 --> 00:18:01.700
Honey, you are always like this!

00:18:00.140 --> 00:18:04.640
Kitasan Black
Arima Kinen
\hSupport Sale
\h1 Onion
\h1 Yen

00:18:02.530 --> 00:18:05.510
How am I supposed to tell what this thing
is or that thing is if that's all you say?

00:18:04.330 --> 00:18:06.650
I mean, you know, it's the thing...

00:18:09.400 --> 00:18:13.400
Kitasan Black
Arima Kinen
Support Sale

00:18:09.400 --> 00:18:14.000
Step right up! We've got
plenty of fresh catches!

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:15.670
Here we go.

00:18:15.670 --> 00:18:17.620
Got some nice carrots.

00:18:17.620 --> 00:18:18.910
Take some!

00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:21.290
A-Are you sure?

00:18:21.290 --> 00:18:25.840
Sure I'm sure. Take 'em home
and have yourself a nice meal.

00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:26.910
Oh, in that case,

00:18:27.210 --> 00:18:29.830
we've got these tomatoes
for you too, Kita-chan.

00:18:29.830 --> 00:18:31.340
They're nice and sweet!

00:18:31.340 --> 00:18:32.970
O-Oh, come on, I couldn't!

00:18:32.970 --> 00:18:37.160
Yes, you could! It's the
least we can do for you.

00:18:38.170 --> 00:18:42.180
You're the star of this market.
We all care about you.

00:18:43.590 --> 00:18:44.930
A star...

00:18:51.260 --> 00:18:52.980
Oh, good idea!

00:18:52.980 --> 00:18:55.980
In that case, take some fish too.

00:18:55.980 --> 00:18:58.090
Try my new product, Kita-chan!

00:18:58.090 --> 00:18:59.500
You like honey, don't you?

00:18:59.500 --> 00:19:01.490
In that case, I've got some steamed buns.

00:19:01.490 --> 00:19:03.430
Got some meat for you too!

00:19:01.490 --> 00:19:10.000
Kitasan Black
Arima Kinen
Support Sale

00:19:03.430 --> 00:19:05.260
Care for some apples?

00:19:05.260 --> 00:19:07.210
Got some baked sweets too.

00:19:07.210 --> 00:19:10.000
There you go! Picked out some
of the freshest for you.

00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:12.250
Come on, she can't take all of that!

00:19:12.250 --> 00:19:15.500
In that case, take one of my baskets.

00:19:20.250 --> 00:19:22.880
I-I... this is...

00:19:22.880 --> 00:19:25.260
This is all we can really do,

00:19:25.260 --> 00:19:27.120
but know that we're rooting for you.

00:19:27.120 --> 00:19:31.320
Yeah. The Arima Kinen was fantastic.

00:19:31.320 --> 00:19:33.900
After it was over, my voice was worn out!

00:19:33.900 --> 00:19:36.190
It really was incredible.

00:19:36.190 --> 00:19:38.980
I can't help but tear up
remembering that battle right

00:19:38.980 --> 00:19:41.400
before you crossed the finish line!

00:19:47.910 --> 00:19:51.740
A warm place, full of smiles...

00:19:52.730 --> 00:19:55.790
A place swirling with passion and energy,

00:19:55.790 --> 00:20:01.850
so bright and hot and dazzling
that it makes you dizzy.

00:20:04.610 --> 00:20:08.500
My original dream...

00:20:11.220 --> 00:20:14.370
I thought I had set it aside.

00:20:16.220 --> 00:20:18.970
I thought I had given up...

00:20:25.280 --> 00:20:28.550
Kita-chan?! What's wrong? You feeling okay?

00:20:28.550 --> 00:20:31.080
N-no, it's not like that...

00:20:31.080 --> 00:20:33.720
I just... well... well!

00:20:35.480 --> 00:20:39.670
Thank you all so much!

00:20:38.780 --> 00:20:39.670
Whoa, wait!

00:20:40.800 --> 00:20:41.920
Kita-chan!

00:20:42.710 --> 00:20:44.540
Kita-chan?!

00:20:46.590 --> 00:20:49.590
Where the heck has Kita-chan gone?

00:20:51.800 --> 00:20:52.680
I'm home!

00:20:52.680 --> 00:20:54.460
Welcome back, Kita-chan.

00:20:54.460 --> 00:20:56.690
What's with all that stuff?

00:20:56.690 --> 00:20:58.440
Heading out!

00:21:02.680 --> 00:21:05.200
Ah, so fresh and so clean!

00:21:05.450 --> 00:21:07.850
Fresh and clean...

00:21:18.140 --> 00:21:19.750
Go for it, Kita-chan.

00:21:21.420 --> 00:21:24.560
I love it when everyone's smiling.

00:21:26.300 --> 00:21:30.390
I love things like festivals that
are filled with those smiles.

00:21:30.920 --> 00:21:34.520
The scene that Teio-san
created on that day...

00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:37.820
I can't help how much I love it.

00:21:38.570 --> 00:21:42.480
I couldn't become Teio-san.
I can't be glamorous.

00:21:42.880 --> 00:21:47.440
I'm not gifted... so I gave up.

00:21:48.700 --> 00:21:52.850
For so long, things haven't
gone the way I imagined,

00:21:52.850 --> 00:21:55.010
and that's bound to continue.

00:21:55.660 --> 00:22:00.400
I can't be a prodigy. I can't become a star.

00:22:00.930 --> 00:22:01.920
I know that...

00:22:02.320 --> 00:22:03.800
I know that,

00:22:04.330 --> 00:22:07.070
but still! I don't want to give up!

00:22:07.810 --> 00:22:11.430
I want to chase after it again! Pick up
where I left off with that dream!

00:22:11.720 --> 00:22:14.930
I want to create a scene like that!

00:22:15.550 --> 00:22:17.140
And that's what I'm gonna do!

